{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/layout\/sizethatfits(proposal:subviews:cache:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/sizeThatFits(proposal:subviews:cache:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sizeThatFits"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"proposal"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore16ProposedViewSizeV","text":"ProposedViewSize","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ProposedViewSize"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"subviews"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore6LayoutP8Subviewsa","text":"Subviews","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/Subviews"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cache"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"inout"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore6LayoutP5CacheQa","text":"Cache","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/Cache"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGSize","text":"CGSize"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"proposal","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A size proposal for the container. The container’s parent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view that calls this method might call the method more than once","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with different proposals to learn more about the container’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"flexibility before deciding which proposal to use for placement.","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"subviews","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A collection of proxies that represent the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"views that the container arranges. You can use the proxies in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"collection to get information about the subviews as you determine","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"how much space the container needs to display them.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"cache","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional storage for calculated data that you can share among"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the methods of your custom layout container. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/makeCache(subviews:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A size that indicates how much space the container"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"needs to arrange its subviews."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement this method to tell your custom layout container’s parent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view how much space the container needs for a set of subviews, given"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a size proposal. The parent might call this method more than once"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"during a layout pass with different proposed sizes to test the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"flexibility of the container, using proposals like:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ProposedViewSize\/zero","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proposal; respond with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layout’s minimum size."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ProposedViewSize\/infinity","isActive":true},{"text":" proposal; respond with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layout’s maximum size.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ProposedViewSize\/unspecified","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proposal; respond with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layout’s ideal size."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The parent might also choose to test flexibility in one dimension at a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time. For example, a horizontal stack might propose a fixed height and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an infinite width, and then the same height with a zero width."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example calculates the size for a basic vertical stack"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that places views in a column, with no spacing between the views:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["private struct BasicVStack: Layout {","    func sizeThatFits(","        proposal: ProposedViewSize,","        subviews: Subviews,","        cache: inout ()","    ) -> CGSize {","        subviews.reduce(CGSize.zero) { result, subview in","            let size = subview.sizeThatFits(.unspecified)","            return CGSize(","                width: max(result.width, size.width),","                height: result.height + size.height)","        }","    }","","    \/\/ This layout also needs a placeSubviews() implementation.","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation asks each subview for its ideal size by calling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LayoutSubview\/sizeThatFits(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method with an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ProposedViewSize\/unspecified","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" proposed size.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It then reduces these values into a single size that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the maximum subview width and the sum of subview heights.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Because this example isn’t flexible, it ignores its size proposal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"input and always returns the same value for a given set of subviews.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OpenSwiftUI views choose their own size, so the layout engine always","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"uses a value that you return from this method as the actual size of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"composite view. That size factors into the construction of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"bounds","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"input to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/placeSubviews(in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","type":"reference"},{"te